.TH DISPLAYCTL 1 "2026-06-21" "1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
displayctl \- Multi-monitor display mode controller
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B displayctl
[\fI\-v\fR] [\fI\-\-dry\-run\fR] \fIcommand\fR [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
displayctl controls multi-monitor display modes on Linux. It supports X11 via
xrandr and Wayland via wlr-randr/swaymsg with automatic backend detection.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Show raw backend commands being executed.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Print backend commands without executing them.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B mirror [\-\-primary NAME] [\-\-arrange LAYOUT]
Duplicate the primary display to all connected monitors.
.TP
.B extend [\-\-primary NAME] [\-\-arrange LAYOUT]
Extend desktop across all monitors (default: left-to-right).
.TP
.B second
Disable primary display, activate secondary only.
.TP
.B pc
Disable external displays, activate internal/primary only.
.TP
.B status
Show all connected displays and current mode in a rich table.
.TP
.B list
List monitors with resolution, refresh rate, and EDID name.
.TP
.B set \-\-mode MODE [\-\-primary NAME] [\-\-arrange LAYOUT]
Set display mode explicitly.
.TP
.B brightness VALUE [\-\-display NAME]
Set brightness (0\-100) on all or specified display.
.TP
.B resolution RESOLUTION \-\-display NAME
Set resolution (e.g. 1920x1080) on specified display.
.TP
.B refresh HZ \-\-display NAME
Set refresh rate on specified display.
.TP
.B rotate ROTATION \-\-display NAME
Set rotation (normal|left|right|inverted) on specified display.
.TP
.B save \-\-profile NAME
Save current display layout as a named profile.
.TP
.B load \-\-profile NAME
Restore a saved display layout.
.TP
.B profiles
List all saved profiles.
.TP
.B delete \-\-profile NAME
Delete a saved profile.
.TP
.B watch [\-\-trigger]
Daemon mode: auto-apply profile on monitor hotplug.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/displayctl/profiles.json
User profiles.
.TP
.I /etc/displayctl/config.json
System-wide configuration.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/displayctl/displayctl.log
Log file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
displayctl mirror
Duplicate all screens.
.TP
displayctl extend
Extend desktop across monitors.
.TP
displayctl save \-\-profile home
Save current layout as "home".
.TP
displayctl load \-\-profile home
Restore "home" layout.
.TP
displayctl watch
Start hotplug daemon.
.SH BACKEND AUTO-DETECTION
displayctl detects the display server via $XDG_SESSION_TYPE or $WAYLAND_DISPLAY.
On X11 it uses xrandr; on Wayland it uses wlr-randr or swaymsg.
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR xrandr (1),
.IR wlr-randr (1),
.IR swaymsg (1)
